{"accepted":[{"assertion":"Formal-Conjectures statement: Erdos32.erdos_32 https://google-deepmind.github.io/formal-conjectures/theorem/?name=Erdos32.erdos_32.","id":"vf_94128d182fa8e669","trust":"signed","type":"theoretical"},{"assertion":"Erdős Problem #32: declared status 'open'. Formalized: yes. Is there a set $A\\subset\\mathbb{N}$ such that\\[\\lvert A\\cap\\{1,\\ldots,N\\}\\rvert = o((\\log N)^2)\\]and such that every large integer can be written as $p+a$ for some prime $p$ and $a\\in A$?\n\nCan the bound $O(\\log N)$ be achieved? Must such an $A$ satisfy\\[\\liminf \\frac{\\lvert A\\cap\\{1,\\ldots,N\\}\\rvert}{\\log N}> 1?\\] Current best: Erd\\H{o}s \\cite{Er54} proved that such a set $A$ exists with $\\lvert A\\cap\\{1,\\ldots,N\\}\\rvert\\ll (\\log N)^2$ (improving a previous result of Lorentz \\cite{Lo54} who achieved $\\ll (\\log N)^3$). Prize: no. Tags: additive basis, number theory.","id":"vf_ce777e50980a741a","trust":"signed","type":"theoretical"}],"accepted_activity":false,"activity":[],"activity_types":[],"attempt_count":0,"banked_attempt_count":0,"commits":[],"dependency_impact":"none","detail_url":"problems/32.json","draft_proposals":[],"edges":[{"evidence":"Problem identity derived from the accepted finding's pinned source anchor.","inferred":true,"relation":"describes","source":"vf_94128d182fa8e669","source_root":"sha256:540d4967071425f77c693e61f62053208b07d67667490dcb9eeef62ec3f1d316","target":"erdos:32","trust":"signed"},{"evidence":"Materialized typed link between accepted findings.","inferred":true,"relation":"synthesized_from","source":"vf_94128d182fa8e669","source_root":"sha256:540d4967071425f77c693e61f62053208b07d67667490dcb9eeef62ec3f1d316","target":"vf_ce777e50980a741a","trust":"signed"},{"evidence":"Problem identity derived from the accepted finding's pinned source anchor.","inferred":true,"relation":"describes","source":"vf_ce777e50980a741a","source_root":"sha256:540d4967071425f77c693e61f62053208b07d67667490dcb9eeef62ec3f1d316","targ